1
00:00:05,958 --> 00:00:07,958
[tense music playing]

2
00:00:15,041 --> 00:00:16,333
[Shimura groans]

3
00:00:20,875 --> 00:00:22,500
This is a warning.

4
00:00:32,541 --> 00:00:33,750
Shimura?

5
00:00:35,416 --> 00:00:36,333
Shimura!

6
00:00:36,875 --> 00:00:37,791
Shimura!

7
00:00:40,583 --> 00:00:41,666
Aki.

8
00:00:44,166 --> 00:00:45,333
Are you okay?

9
00:00:45,958 --> 00:00:46,791
[groans]

10
00:00:47,666 --> 00:00:49,416
I wasn't much of a fighter.

11
00:00:50,125 --> 00:00:51,333
At least you're okay.

12
00:00:51,416 --> 00:00:52,916
We've other issues now.

13
00:00:55,458 --> 00:00:56,291
A warning?

14
00:00:56,375 --> 00:00:58,041
But why Shimura?

15
00:00:58,125 --> 00:01:00,958
Someone's jealous because we're popular,
so they attack Shimura?

16
00:01:01,041 --> 00:01:02,291
Maybe.

17
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:05,458
You reek of alcohol.

18
00:01:05,958 --> 00:01:08,083
Oh, no.
You're imagining things. [chuckles]

19
00:01:08,166 --> 00:01:09,541
I'm underage, you know?

20
00:01:09,625 --> 00:01:11,208
I tell you what…

21
00:01:11,291 --> 00:01:13,958
if something like this happens again,
then next time I'm gonna--

22
00:01:14,041 --> 00:01:15,208
It's very fishy.

23
00:01:15,291 --> 00:01:16,791
Do I smell that bad?

24
00:01:16,875 --> 00:01:18,583
These events are too coincidental.

25
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:19,750
- I agree.
- [sniffing]

26
00:01:19,833 --> 00:01:23,291
It's likely that the hacker
and your attackers are the same guys.

27
00:01:23,375 --> 00:01:24,583
Oh, now I get it.

28
00:01:24,666 --> 00:01:26,041
But how did they do it?

29
00:01:26,125 --> 00:01:28,583
Our username and passwords
are very secure.

30
00:01:28,666 --> 00:01:30,083
It beats me too.

31
00:01:30,583 --> 00:01:33,458
Unless somehow,
they got their hands on our password.

32
00:01:33,541 --> 00:01:34,708
But how?

33
00:01:37,250 --> 00:01:38,791
- Kanegon.
- Hmm?

34
00:01:38,875 --> 00:01:41,875
You didn't fall for some phishing scheme
on a porn site, did you?

35
00:01:41,958 --> 00:01:44,583
Oh, come on.
I'm not a pervert or anything.

36
00:01:46,208 --> 00:01:49,583
Hey, Kanegon. Show us how you edit.

37
00:01:49,666 --> 00:01:50,625
You really wanna know?

38
00:01:50,708 --> 00:01:52,416
- Yes!
- No. Wait, really?

39
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:54,083
Okay. [laughs]

40
00:01:54,166 --> 00:01:55,583
- Oh, this is so great.
- [phone beeps]

41
00:01:55,666 --> 00:01:58,791
- [Toru] Let me see, V-I-R-A-L.
- [girl 1] Viral.

42
00:01:58,875 --> 00:02:03,083
- [Toru] H-I-and-T
- [girl 2] Ah!

43
00:02:03,166 --> 00:02:04,583
[girl 1] Don't forget the password.

44
00:02:04,666 --> 00:02:06,708
[Toru] K-K-D…

45
00:02:06,791 --> 00:02:07,833
[whimpers] Oh.

46
00:02:07,916 --> 00:02:09,916
Hmm? What's wrong?

47
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,000
[Toru] Oh no.

48
00:02:12,125 --> 00:02:13,250
It's nothing

49
00:02:17,833 --> 00:02:20,208
HIGH SCHOOL

50
00:02:23,458 --> 00:02:26,625
- Oh, hi. I had a great time last night--
- I'm sure you did.

51
00:02:26,708 --> 00:02:30,041
- If you want the girls' info--
- [Toru] The password!

52
00:02:31,166 --> 00:02:32,291
You stole it.

53
00:02:33,041 --> 00:02:34,166
What? I don't know.

54
00:02:34,666 --> 00:02:37,125
- You're making things up.
- Don't play dumb with me.

55
00:02:37,208 --> 00:02:40,333
You got our account suspended
and you had those guys ambush Shimura.

56
00:02:40,416 --> 00:02:42,583
What do you mean?
What are you accusing me of?

57
00:02:42,666 --> 00:02:44,083
I don't have time for this.

58
00:02:44,166 --> 00:02:45,166
[gasps]

59
00:02:45,250 --> 00:02:48,666
Recently, I joined an agency. So I'm busy.

60
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:51,125
- Have a good day.
- Hey! Wait, you…

61
00:02:53,166 --> 00:02:54,666
God dammit!

62
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:57,333
What am I going to do?

63
00:02:57,416 --> 00:02:59,208
[pop music playing over speakers]

64
00:02:59,291 --> 00:03:00,625
- Good work today.
- [Kaho] You too.

65
00:03:02,041 --> 00:03:04,125
- What happened to you?
- Huh?

66
00:03:04,208 --> 00:03:05,458
Your head.

67
00:03:06,375 --> 00:03:07,833
Oh, this.

68
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:10,000
Did you fight again?

69
00:03:10,083 --> 00:03:13,166
Uh, no, I didn't. I got ambushed.

70
00:03:13,250 --> 00:03:14,791
It was two against one.

71
00:03:14,875 --> 00:03:16,125
I didn't stand a chance.

72
00:03:16,208 --> 00:03:17,666
Who did this to you?

73
00:03:17,750 --> 00:03:20,208
I don't know. But, don't worry.

74
00:03:20,291 --> 00:03:21,916
Next time, they don't stand a chance.

75
00:03:22,708 --> 00:03:23,958
[chuckles]

76
00:03:24,041 --> 00:03:27,791
Oh, here.
I forgot to return this. Thank you.

77
00:03:27,875 --> 00:03:29,500
Oh, thank you.

78
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:32,708
[gate slams]

79
00:03:36,541 --> 00:03:38,250
- [pop music continues]
- Uh, can I…

80
00:03:38,333 --> 00:03:39,375
Huh?

81
00:03:39,458 --> 00:03:43,000
Oh, yeah.
I was wondering about our café date.

82
00:03:43,083 --> 00:03:45,000
Ah! [giggles]

83
00:03:45,083 --> 00:03:46,250
I'll let you know, yeah?

84
00:03:47,291 --> 00:03:50,250
- Well, better get back to it.
- Yeah, I'll be right there.

85
00:03:52,916 --> 00:03:54,375
[phone buzzing]

86
00:03:57,041 --> 00:03:58,208
I KNOW WHO DID IT

87
00:03:58,291 --> 00:03:59,541
Kanegon?

88
00:04:02,666 --> 00:04:07,500
[Rumi] Hey, so I heard
that <i>Viral Hit</i>'s account got hacked.

89
00:04:08,041 --> 00:04:09,250
Really?

90
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:11,125
Mr. Kimishima, was that you?

91
00:04:11,208 --> 00:04:13,333
[laughs] And why would I do that?

92
00:04:14,208 --> 00:04:17,083
Anyway, this is good.
Now you don't have them to worry about.

93
00:04:18,250 --> 00:04:19,208
Hmm.

94
00:04:20,166 --> 00:04:23,625
But… I really want more followers.

95
00:04:23,708 --> 00:04:25,875
[chuckles] Oh, I know.

96
00:04:28,041 --> 00:04:32,708
I told you.
I'll do anything for you, Rumi. Hmm?

97
00:04:33,666 --> 00:04:35,000
[chuckles] Mm-hmm.

98
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,625
[Shimura] <i>Influencer agency?</i>

99
00:04:47,708 --> 00:04:50,166
Yeah. Rumi recently joined an agency.

100
00:04:50,250 --> 00:04:51,375
That's it there.

101
00:04:52,666 --> 00:04:55,083
CANDY CROWN
CREATOR

102
00:04:55,833 --> 00:04:59,083
- There she is.
- Not the point. Keep scrolling down.

103
00:05:04,083 --> 00:05:06,250
Hey! These are the guys who attacked me.

104
00:05:06,333 --> 00:05:07,833
Yeah, I thought so.

105
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:10,500
Now all the dots are connected.

106
00:05:10,583 --> 00:05:14,166
We need to solve this quickly
so I can redeem myself to Aki.

107
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:15,958
Redeem yourself? Why?

108
00:05:17,875 --> 00:05:21,708
- What's Aki got to do with…
- Come on! You know I have a crush on her.

109
00:05:22,833 --> 00:05:26,458
- No.
- Hey, you haven't figured that out yet?

110
00:05:26,541 --> 00:05:27,916
Uh, no.

111
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:31,333
[Toru] Jeez. We need
an emergency meeting now.

112
00:05:32,083 --> 00:05:33,583
At Aki's!

113
00:05:34,291 --> 00:05:35,458
Come on!

114
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:38,750
[Shimura] How long has this been going on?

115
00:05:39,250 --> 00:05:40,083
PINGURI

116
00:05:40,166 --> 00:05:44,583
They've got 600 subscribers who post
videos doing obnoxious shit in public.

117
00:05:44,666 --> 00:05:47,916
And you think it was Rumi
who had them attack me, right?

118
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:50,958
She denied it, but there's
no doubt they're connected.

119
00:05:51,458 --> 00:05:53,791
They got hold of my password
after she stole it.

120
00:05:53,875 --> 00:05:57,875
Mmm.  Let's go to police.
There's no doubt that this is a crime.

121
00:05:59,083 --> 00:06:00,750
[Toru] I know where you're coming from,

122
00:06:00,833 --> 00:06:04,083
but if we do that, our channel,
it could get taken down.

123
00:06:06,208 --> 00:06:08,291
Young people are flocking
to the streaming app

124
00:06:08,375 --> 00:06:09,791
that we've been using.

125
00:06:09,875 --> 00:06:12,750
But since it's so new,
there's no oversight.

126
00:06:12,833 --> 00:06:14,250
That's how we do what we do.

127
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:17,791
If they find out
we're making money by using violence,

128
00:06:17,875 --> 00:06:20,208
they'll ban our account immediately.

129
00:06:20,708 --> 00:06:23,000
So, what are you saying?
We should forget it?

130
00:06:23,083 --> 00:06:27,791
- [tense music playing]
- We've just found our next opponent.

131
00:06:28,833 --> 00:06:32,125
They trapped you, they think,
but you allowed it. Didn't you?

132
00:06:33,125 --> 00:06:36,041
Hang on a sec.
There are two of them, yeah?

133
00:06:36,125 --> 00:06:38,416
I was off my guard when they attacked.

134
00:06:38,916 --> 00:06:42,500
We'll be bringing down streamers
who attack members of the public.

135
00:06:43,125 --> 00:06:45,208
Good content, it'll make money.

136
00:06:46,833 --> 00:06:49,166
HOW TO BEAT A THUG IN A FIGHT

137
00:06:49,250 --> 00:06:51,666
Can I really win by listening to you?

138
00:06:53,916 --> 00:06:55,250
[groaning]

139
00:07:00,083 --> 00:07:03,583
How am I supposed to fight
two guys at once?

140
00:07:04,666 --> 00:07:06,000
[phone chimes]

141
00:07:06,666 --> 00:07:07,708
NEW VIDEO ALERT

142
00:07:10,958 --> 00:07:12,916
HOW TO WIN AGAINST MULTIPLE OPPONENTS

143
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,666
- Yes!
- [rhythmic electronic music playing]

144
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:19,541
[TOU-KEI] <i>What happens when a person</i>
<i>with zero training in martial arts</i>

145
00:07:19,625 --> 00:07:22,916
<i>attempts to fight</i>
<i>multiple opponents at once?</i>

146
00:07:23,416 --> 00:07:25,666
<i>He will never win.</i>

147
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:29,916
Yeah. But you're gonna show me
some new moves now, aren't you?

148
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:32,791
<i>If you are serious about winning,</i>

149
00:07:32,875 --> 00:07:36,041
<i>you must master</i>
<i>at least ten of my techniques.</i>

150
00:07:36,125 --> 00:07:37,166
Ten? Wow.

151
00:07:37,250 --> 00:07:38,916
That's kind of a lot…

152
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:39,916
[inhales through teeth]

153
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,208
[TOU-KEI] <i>That's right. In other words,</i>

154
00:07:42,291 --> 00:07:45,375
<i>there's no chance</i>
<i>for a beginner like you to win.</i>

155
00:07:45,458 --> 00:07:47,833
You cannot win against multiple opponents.

156
00:07:47,916 --> 00:07:49,750
<i>So give up.</i>

157
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:51,750
What? You serious?

158
00:07:51,833 --> 00:07:54,500
I… oh… come on! There's nothing?

159
00:07:54,583 --> 00:07:55,791
[TOU-KEI] <i>However,</i>

160
00:07:55,875 --> 00:08:00,125
<i>even if you can't win the fight,</i>
<i>you can still win the game.</i>

161
00:08:02,125 --> 00:08:03,500
URABE GENERAL HOSPITAL

162
00:08:03,541 --> 00:08:06,625
I'm glad to hear
your son is enjoying school.

163
00:08:06,708 --> 00:08:08,666
I think he's made some good friends.

164
00:08:08,750 --> 00:08:10,500
He's been so lively lately.

165
00:08:10,583 --> 00:08:13,250
Your son is busy enjoying his age!

166
00:08:13,333 --> 00:08:14,916
He's already in high school.

167
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,750
- What if he starts dating someone?
- [laughs]

168
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:18,875
[woman] Now, we have a meeting
at 10:00 today.

169
00:08:18,958 --> 00:08:19,791
Yes, I'm aware.

170
00:08:19,875 --> 00:08:21,125
Great work today.

171
00:08:21,916 --> 00:08:24,041
- Good morning.
- Hello, Director. Good morning.

172
00:08:24,666 --> 00:08:27,541
Oh, look, are you feeling better today?

173
00:08:27,625 --> 00:08:29,250
I have good and bad days.

174
00:08:29,750 --> 00:08:33,583
Don't worry. With us working together,
we'll beat this thing.

175
00:08:33,666 --> 00:08:35,625
- Thank you.
- Mm.

176
00:08:39,291 --> 00:08:41,625
[nurse] The director's
such a wonderful man.

177
00:08:41,708 --> 00:08:44,041
[tense music playing]

178
00:08:45,916 --> 00:08:47,625
KABUKICHO

179
00:08:47,708 --> 00:08:48,750
Hello!

180
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:51,083
- I'm Pink! Yeah!
- Green! Yeah!

181
00:08:51,166 --> 00:08:53,916
Tonight we're hitting the nightlife
to prank some people!

182
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:54,875
Whoo!

183
00:08:54,958 --> 00:08:57,791
Which unsuspecting victim
will give us the best reaction?

184
00:08:57,875 --> 00:08:59,416
- It's showtime!
- Woo-hoo!

185
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:01,916
- Hey, hey. What about that girl? Woo-hoo!
- Yo!

186
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,500
- He went for it!
- [woman 1] So cute.

187
00:09:03,583 --> 00:09:05,375
- [woman 2] Yeah, he's gorgeous.
- [Pink] Miss!

188
00:09:05,458 --> 00:09:07,333
- There's a snake on you.
- [both scream]

189
00:09:07,416 --> 00:09:09,208
Whoa! Oh my God!

190
00:09:09,291 --> 00:09:10,291
[Green and Pink] Just run!

191
00:09:10,375 --> 00:09:12,041
- [Pink] Come on, run!
- [Green] Just run!

192
00:09:12,125 --> 00:09:13,625
[Pink] Run some more!

193
00:09:14,458 --> 00:09:16,416
[Shimura] You bastards.

194
00:09:16,500 --> 00:09:19,458
That's quite enough of your bullshit.

195
00:09:19,541 --> 00:09:22,375
[militant music playing]

196
00:09:23,416 --> 00:09:25,208
[Aki] <i>Time to go live.</i>

197
00:09:27,458 --> 00:09:28,541
DID HE GET TALLER?

198
00:09:28,625 --> 00:09:29,916
IT'S A GROWTH SPURT LOL

199
00:09:31,291 --> 00:09:33,416
You're the guy from <i>Viral Hit</i>?

200
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:35,208
[Green] Why the hell are you here?

201
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:38,000
GET 'EM, SHIMURA! LOL

202
00:09:38,083 --> 00:09:39,000
TOO FUNNY LOL

203
00:09:39,083 --> 00:09:43,041
We're starting now.
The <i>Viral Hit </i>live stream.

204
00:09:48,708 --> 00:09:51,708
[TOU-KEI] <i>How to win</i>
<i>against multiple opponents.</i>

205
00:09:52,208 --> 00:09:55,375
<i>The answer lies in your nature.</i>

206
00:09:56,125 --> 00:09:59,333
<i>It's bluff and intimidation.</i>

207
00:10:00,125 --> 00:10:04,541
<i>The bluff of a mantis,</i>
<i>fending off an attacker for survival!</i>

208
00:10:05,166 --> 00:10:09,916
<i>The intimidation of a gorilla defending</i>
<i>his rank in the hierarchy.</i>

209
00:10:11,166 --> 00:10:15,125
<i>Now, show them</i>
<i>that you can take them all on,</i>

210
00:10:16,041 --> 00:10:18,333
<i>even though you're alone.</i>

211
00:10:18,416 --> 00:10:20,500
<i>Last time you caught me off guard.</i>

212
00:10:20,583 --> 00:10:24,291
<i>I can take you both on. Not an issue.</i>

213
00:10:24,375 --> 00:10:25,333
[grunts] Heh!

214
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:27,000
[TOU-KEI] <i>The bluff of a mantis!</i>

215
00:10:27,666 --> 00:10:30,583
Give me the new password
and get the hell out of here…

216
00:10:30,666 --> 00:10:31,875
[gruffly] …or I'll kill both of you!

217
00:10:31,958 --> 00:10:33,791
[TOU-KEI] <i>Intimidation of a gorilla!</i>

218
00:10:34,416 --> 00:10:36,375
Whoa, wait a minute.
We're already live, so…

219
00:10:36,458 --> 00:10:37,708
[Green] That's right.

220
00:10:37,791 --> 00:10:38,750
[both chuckle]

221
00:10:39,250 --> 00:10:40,333
[TOU-KEI] <i>However,</i>

222
00:10:40,416 --> 00:10:43,458
<i>you must never forget this one point.</i>

223
00:10:43,541 --> 00:10:46,416
<i>Don't ever let your opponent catch on…</i>

224
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:47,583
[groans]

225
00:10:48,208 --> 00:10:50,791
<i>…to your bluff and intimidation.</i>

226
00:10:52,166 --> 00:10:53,875
- You idiot. What are you doing?
- I just…

227
00:10:53,958 --> 00:10:56,458
[Pink] Hey, wait a minute. Look at this.

228
00:10:57,083 --> 00:10:59,708
His shoes are full of all these insoles.

229
00:10:59,791 --> 00:11:01,416
[both laughing]

230
00:11:01,958 --> 00:11:03,291
Dipshit.

231
00:11:03,791 --> 00:11:05,500
Do you think
we're dumb or something? Huh?

232
00:11:05,583 --> 00:11:07,875
- [Shimura] Hey! Hey!
- [Green] Don't mess with us.

233
00:11:07,958 --> 00:11:08,791
[laughs]

234
00:11:08,875 --> 00:11:11,916
[Shimura] <i>Damn it. I can't hear</i>
<i>the master's voice anymore.</i>

235
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,166
<i>What should I do?</i>

236
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:15,166
- What's this? What's this!
- Stop it. I said stop!

237
00:11:15,250 --> 00:11:17,000
- Come on! Show me!
- [Shimura groans]

238
00:11:17,083 --> 00:11:18,541
- We're gone.
- [Green] Show me!

239
00:11:18,625 --> 00:11:20,708
- [laughing]
- Look at his shoulder!

240
00:11:20,791 --> 00:11:22,833
<i>- </i>[Green] <i>It's all padded. It's fake!</i>
- [laughing]

241
00:11:22,916 --> 00:11:24,333
SHOULDER PADS ARE SO 80S

242
00:11:24,416 --> 00:11:25,500
THIS IS HILARIOUS

243
00:11:25,583 --> 00:11:26,625
[Pink] He's such a loser!

244
00:11:26,708 --> 00:11:28,250
[rhythmic drum music playing]

245
00:11:28,333 --> 00:11:31,125
[both laughing]

246
00:11:31,208 --> 00:11:33,916
I can't stand your type of person.

247
00:11:34,875 --> 00:11:36,083
It's time.

248
00:11:36,166 --> 00:11:38,250
Beatdown time!

249
00:11:38,333 --> 00:11:39,666
- [grunts]
- [groans] Ah!

250
00:11:39,750 --> 00:11:40,875
[Pink] Don't mess with us.

251
00:11:40,958 --> 00:11:42,625
- Take…
- [growls]

252
00:11:42,708 --> 00:11:45,166
- [both straining, grunting]
- [suspenseful music playing]

253
00:11:45,250 --> 00:11:46,750
[Pink] Damn it! That hurt, you bastard!

254
00:11:46,833 --> 00:11:48,583
[all grunting]

255
00:11:49,791 --> 00:11:52,500
[Shimura] <i>I don't know.</i>
<i>Something's wrong with me.</i>

256
00:11:52,583 --> 00:11:53,833
[Pink] Ah! Take it!

257
00:11:53,916 --> 00:11:55,666
- This is bad.
- Just wait.

258
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:56,916
- [Green] Yes!
- [grunting]

259
00:11:57,583 --> 00:12:00,625
- [Shimura gasping, grunting]
- [Pink and Green grunting]

260
00:12:02,583 --> 00:12:04,666
- [Shimura] <i>What's happening to me?</i>
<i>- </i>[Pink] Wait! Hey!

261
00:12:06,375 --> 00:12:07,541
[Toru] Come on!

262
00:12:07,625 --> 00:12:09,750
[Pink] Hey! Wait!

263
00:12:10,625 --> 00:12:11,708
[Green] Hey!

264
00:12:11,791 --> 00:12:14,000
[Pink] You're going nowhere! Hey!

265
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,750
- [Green] Wait!
<i>- </i>[Shimura] <i>I'm scared to death.</i>

266
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:21,291
<i>- But at the same time, kinda pumped.</i>
- [Pink and Green yelling]

267
00:12:25,458 --> 00:12:30,291
VIRAL HIT

268
00:12:30,375 --> 00:12:31,541
[motors revving]

269
00:12:37,583 --> 00:12:39,125
- [Shimura panting]
- [Pink] Wait up!

270
00:12:39,208 --> 00:12:40,291
Damn it!

271
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:44,291
Bastard! Stop running away! Hey!

272
00:12:44,375 --> 00:12:47,625
[Shimura continues panting] Ah! Ah!

273
00:12:47,708 --> 00:12:48,875
[Pink growls]

274
00:12:52,708 --> 00:12:54,666
Catch him! Hey! Hey!

275
00:12:56,416 --> 00:12:58,125
Get over here, bastard.

276
00:12:58,208 --> 00:13:00,333
[motors revving]

277
00:13:00,416 --> 00:13:03,083
- [Pink] Hey, stop!
- [Shimura grunting]

278
00:13:03,166 --> 00:13:04,500
- [Pink] Hey!
- [man] Look out!

279
00:13:05,458 --> 00:13:08,000
- [both grunting]
- [tires screeching]

280
00:13:09,583 --> 00:13:11,583
[both yelping]

281
00:13:11,666 --> 00:13:13,625
[boys yelping]

282
00:13:13,708 --> 00:13:16,541
- Calf kick! Calf kick!
- [Green and Pink howl]

283
00:13:16,625 --> 00:13:18,291
[grunting]

284
00:13:18,375 --> 00:13:21,708
[Pink] Wait! Hey, you! Come back!

285
00:13:27,166 --> 00:13:29,625
[Shimura grunting]

286
00:13:29,708 --> 00:13:32,750
- [tires screeching]
- [Shimura yelping]

287
00:13:32,833 --> 00:13:34,750
[Pink] You have to let it go!

288
00:13:36,583 --> 00:13:38,750
- Calf kick! [grunts]
- [Pink yowls]

289
00:13:39,250 --> 00:13:42,125
- [Pink wails] Ow!
- [Shimura grunting, panting]

290
00:13:42,208 --> 00:13:44,208
[Green] Ugh! That really hurt.

291
00:13:44,291 --> 00:13:45,916
[Pink] You bastard.

292
00:13:46,875 --> 00:13:48,541
I won't forgive you!

293
00:13:48,625 --> 00:13:50,583
- [Pink and Green gasping]
- [Aki] That's enough!

294
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,791
The match is over, can't you see?

295
00:13:55,416 --> 00:13:57,958
Huh? Who the hell are you?

296
00:13:59,041 --> 00:14:02,375
You know much better than anyone
how exhausted you must be.

297
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,583
[Green] Don't mess with us.

298
00:14:05,250 --> 00:14:08,958
- We're not leaving until this is finished.
- All right then, go ahead.

299
00:14:10,166 --> 00:14:13,375
That is, if you don't care
that you look like a couple of asses.

300
00:14:14,416 --> 00:14:15,750
MISSED THE BEST BIT LOL

301
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:17,041
KEEP UP, CAMERAMAN!

302
00:14:18,416 --> 00:14:19,708
[panting]

303
00:14:21,500 --> 00:14:24,166
Hand over the password, then go home.

304
00:14:26,666 --> 00:14:27,791
- Shit!
- [both thud]

305
00:14:27,875 --> 00:14:29,958
[Green groans] Shit!

306
00:14:33,708 --> 00:14:35,083
PASSWORD CHANGE COMPLETE

307
00:14:35,166 --> 00:14:36,625
[Ai] Everything's back to normal.

308
00:14:37,375 --> 00:14:38,875
I've changed the password again.

309
00:14:38,958 --> 00:14:42,125
Yeah! I didn't expect you
to put up a fight like this.

310
00:14:42,208 --> 00:14:44,916
When they started at you,
I thought you were done! [chuckles]

311
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:50,166
Yes, that's right.
Well… have I just gone nuts?

312
00:14:51,541 --> 00:14:53,750
I don't fully understand it either.

313
00:14:53,833 --> 00:14:58,083
At some point,
I was afraid, but also fearless.

314
00:14:58,166 --> 00:15:01,583
Like… like I was pumped, you know?

315
00:15:01,666 --> 00:15:04,791
That's so great.
Main thing is you're okay.

316
00:15:04,875 --> 00:15:07,500
Maybe I'm not okay at all. [laughs]

317
00:15:08,083 --> 00:15:09,833
[driving electronic music playing]

318
00:15:10,166 --> 00:15:13,500
Hello there. I apologize
to all of you about the recent suspension.

319
00:15:13,583 --> 00:15:15,291
- CONGRATS ON YOUR COMEBACK
- YOU WENT THROUGH HELL

320
00:15:15,375 --> 00:15:18,916
Our main channel was hijacked
by some nasty trolls.

321
00:15:19,416 --> 00:15:22,291
My recent fight you saw on the subchannel,

322
00:15:22,375 --> 00:15:24,625
you can now see on my main channel.

323
00:15:24,708 --> 00:15:27,875
Oh, and please, keep up the donations!

324
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,250
- [device beeps]
- Okay!

325
00:15:31,208 --> 00:15:32,541
Aki, how are the donations?

326
00:15:32,625 --> 00:15:35,250
- [Aki] Fantastic donations pouring in.
- [Shimura] All right!

327
00:15:35,333 --> 00:15:37,708
You see, you can't do without me, can you?

328
00:15:37,791 --> 00:15:39,041
You've got a nerve, haven't you?

329
00:15:39,125 --> 00:15:41,250
You're the one
who got us into this trouble.

330
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:42,916
[Toru] Yeah, sorry about that.

331
00:15:44,958 --> 00:15:48,458
Kanegon.
What's next for us then?

332
00:15:49,750 --> 00:15:51,750
[video game sounds bleeping]

333
00:15:54,125 --> 00:15:56,291
[game characters grunting]

334
00:15:58,250 --> 00:16:00,458
[man 1] Hey, when are you gonna quit?

335
00:16:00,541 --> 00:16:01,500
[man 2] Move, damn it!

336
00:16:02,166 --> 00:16:03,250
[game voice] <i>K.O.</i>

337
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,166
I died.

338
00:16:07,250 --> 00:16:09,875
Your turn's over. Over!  Now move it!

339
00:16:09,958 --> 00:16:10,833
Go!

340
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:16,083
[man 2] What, punk? Wanna go?

341
00:16:16,166 --> 00:16:18,750
What are you, <i>Viral Hit 2.0</i>?

342
00:16:19,875 --> 00:16:21,458
[tense music playing]

343
00:16:21,541 --> 00:16:23,125
Give me 100.

344
00:16:23,208 --> 00:16:24,208
[man 1] What?

345
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:30,541
[men groaning]

346
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,291
VIRAL HIT

347
00:16:37,291 --> 00:16:39,458
VIRAL HIT
#3 RECOMMENDED VIDEO

348
00:16:39,541 --> 00:16:41,416
[students screaming on video]

349
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:42,791
[HAMAKEN on video]<i>You little rat!</i>

350
00:16:42,875 --> 00:16:47,291
VIRAL HIT
#1 TOP PICK VIDEO

351
00:16:49,708 --> 00:16:51,375
<i>Viral Hit.</i>

352
00:16:56,416 --> 00:16:57,750
[music fades]

353
00:16:57,833 --> 00:16:59,500
I'll put your fresh clothes here.

354
00:16:59,583 --> 00:17:00,666
Thank you.

355
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:05,833
- Say, have you heard of streamers?
- What?

356
00:17:05,916 --> 00:17:09,833
Kids these days want to be streamers
when they grow up. It says it, just look.

357
00:17:11,708 --> 00:17:13,166
Is that right?

358
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:15,583
#1 DREAM JOB FOR BOYS:
STREAMER

359
00:17:15,666 --> 00:17:17,958
Oh, but I'm not into that. [chuckles]

360
00:17:18,041 --> 00:17:21,375
Of course not.  Why would people want
to watch streaming of you?

361
00:17:21,458 --> 00:17:22,666
[Shimura] Ah, you're right.

362
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:25,875
Oh, maybe I should give it a try.

363
00:17:25,958 --> 00:17:27,750
And who's gonna watch that?

364
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:30,666
Oh, I think I'd be pretty good at it.

365
00:17:30,750 --> 00:17:33,875
Like a mother fighting off
a disease. [laughs]

366
00:17:33,958 --> 00:17:35,291
[chuckles]

367
00:17:36,958 --> 00:17:38,416
Just curious.

368
00:17:39,250 --> 00:17:41,958
What do you think now
that you've read about them?

369
00:17:43,791 --> 00:17:44,666
Why do you ask?

370
00:17:45,375 --> 00:17:48,291
Oh. Like I said, just curious.

371
00:17:50,083 --> 00:17:52,500
I don't see anything wrong with it.

372
00:17:53,708 --> 00:17:57,166
But… I'd be worried as a parent.

373
00:17:58,791 --> 00:18:02,541
I'd rather my child work
a normal job like you do now.

374
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:05,791
I see.

375
00:18:07,708 --> 00:18:10,958
Oh.  It's time for me to get going.

376
00:18:11,041 --> 00:18:13,625
- So busy! Working again?
- No.

377
00:18:14,833 --> 00:18:16,708
There's just something I need to do.

378
00:18:16,791 --> 00:18:18,625
You seeing a <i>girl</i>?

379
00:18:18,708 --> 00:18:21,666
Oh, of course not. No, you're wrong!

380
00:18:21,750 --> 00:18:24,166
Aw. That's too bad.

381
00:18:24,250 --> 00:18:28,000
[both laugh]

382
00:18:30,208 --> 00:18:31,541
VIRAL HIT

383
00:18:31,625 --> 00:18:35,458
[Toru] <i>Viral Hit </i>is looking for fighters.
Refer yourself or others.

384
00:18:35,541 --> 00:18:37,791
All right, it's uploaded.

385
00:18:37,875 --> 00:18:41,500
Oh, look!
It's already got views.

386
00:18:42,333 --> 00:18:43,958
Where's Shimura today?

387
00:18:44,458 --> 00:18:47,208
Who knows?
He said he was busy or something.

388
00:18:47,750 --> 00:18:48,750
Is he working?

389
00:18:48,833 --> 00:18:50,041
Don't think so.

390
00:18:51,083 --> 00:18:54,291
- Oh.
- He's seeing Asamiya.

391
00:18:54,375 --> 00:18:57,041
He was all serious,
saying he had to see her today.

392
00:18:57,125 --> 00:18:59,166
I think it might be a date.

393
00:19:02,458 --> 00:19:07,041
And, you know, it's…
just the two of us here now. Isn't it?

394
00:19:07,125 --> 00:19:09,833
[chuckles] Aren't you nervous, you know?

395
00:19:09,916 --> 00:19:12,416
- [poignant music playing]
- Uh…

396
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:17,916
- So, Aki… do you have a boyfriend?
- [door slams open loudly]

397
00:19:21,125 --> 00:19:23,291
Don't you dare
lay a finger on my daughter.

398
00:19:23,375 --> 00:19:24,416
KYOTO VEGETABLE MIBUNA
BUBUZUKE

399
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:26,750
- Oh, I would never.
- [jaunty music playing]

400
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:29,666
Well, I don't think I trust you.

401
00:19:29,750 --> 00:19:31,791
Oh, that's silly.
What are you talking about, Dad?

402
00:19:31,875 --> 00:19:32,750
Dad?

403
00:19:33,375 --> 00:19:34,250
Aki.

404
00:19:34,833 --> 00:19:38,291
I'm glad that you made friends,
but why do you only bring men around here?

405
00:19:38,375 --> 00:19:40,291
[Aki] Oh, shut up and get back to work.

406
00:19:42,833 --> 00:19:44,666
- Deh!
- [splutters]

407
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:46,041
Hey!

408
00:19:47,166 --> 00:19:48,708
[slides door closed loudly]

409
00:19:50,375 --> 00:19:51,291
Sorry.

410
00:19:51,375 --> 00:19:53,416
[laughs] It's okay.

411
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:57,541
I guess you guys are, um, used to
joking around with each other, yeah?

412
00:19:57,625 --> 00:20:01,125
Uh… he was deadly serious.

413
00:20:02,041 --> 00:20:03,166
Oh, I see.

414
00:20:04,208 --> 00:20:06,541
Where did you live when you were overseas?

415
00:20:06,625 --> 00:20:07,875
We were in the US.

416
00:20:07,958 --> 00:20:10,250
Yeah? That's really great.

417
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:12,958
Dad's work took us there for 12 years.

418
00:20:13,041 --> 00:20:15,041
It… was tough.

419
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:19,416
- [buoyant electronic music playing]
- [birdsong]

420
00:20:28,541 --> 00:20:30,541
[no in-scene audio]

421
00:20:52,125 --> 00:20:54,166
Thank you for paying. Hope it was okay.

422
00:20:54,250 --> 00:20:56,916
It was my way
to thank you for the other day.

423
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,250
That's nice!

424
00:20:59,083 --> 00:21:00,375
Parfait was great!

425
00:21:00,458 --> 00:21:03,083
Mm. You wanted to talk?

426
00:21:03,583 --> 00:21:04,875
Something on your mind?

427
00:21:05,583 --> 00:21:08,250
Oh, right. Uh, yes.

428
00:21:08,750 --> 00:21:11,125
[Shimura] <i>Now I can't make myself ask it.</i>

429
00:21:12,166 --> 00:21:13,666
Asamiya-san…

430
00:21:14,958 --> 00:21:17,416
- Your house, it's fancy.
- Huh?

431
00:21:17,500 --> 00:21:19,625
[Shimura] <i>What the hell am I saying?</i>

432
00:21:20,250 --> 00:21:21,958
Actually, the other day,

433
00:21:22,458 --> 00:21:25,166
I followed you
to return your handkerchief.

434
00:21:25,833 --> 00:21:28,541
Uh, I…I wasn't trying to stalk you.

435
00:21:28,625 --> 00:21:30,333
Mm, I understand.

436
00:21:30,958 --> 00:21:35,166
It just… felt like you and I…
are kind of different.

437
00:21:36,083 --> 00:21:38,875
Your dad must be a very important person.

438
00:21:38,958 --> 00:21:41,791
That's not true. He's fairly normal.

439
00:21:41,875 --> 00:21:43,666
I wondered why you worked part-time.

440
00:21:43,750 --> 00:21:45,541
What's so weird about that?

441
00:21:45,625 --> 00:21:47,708
I guess nothing. [laughs]

442
00:21:47,791 --> 00:21:49,375
So that was it?

443
00:21:49,458 --> 00:21:50,333
Oh.

444
00:21:51,625 --> 00:21:54,666
No. Not entirely.

445
00:21:56,625 --> 00:21:58,083
[music fades].

446
00:22:18,333 --> 00:22:19,666
Another time, I think.

447
00:22:21,666 --> 00:22:22,958
Mm. Okay, then.

448
00:22:23,041 --> 00:22:24,166
[laughs softly]

449
00:22:37,708 --> 00:22:39,791
Guys! [laughs]

450
00:22:41,583 --> 00:22:43,375
I found your next opponent.

451
00:22:43,458 --> 00:22:44,375
Really, who is it?

452
00:22:44,458 --> 00:22:45,833
Shinjo Reo.

453
00:22:46,333 --> 00:22:47,916
He's a Tae kwon do champion.

454
00:22:48,458 --> 00:22:49,458
Tae kwon do?

455
00:22:49,541 --> 00:22:53,125
The thought of you facing off with him
is sending the viewers crazy!

456
00:22:54,416 --> 00:22:57,458
He's a high school dropout
and notorious troublemaker.

457
00:22:58,250 --> 00:23:01,750
They say that he smashes
his wristwatch every fight.

458
00:23:02,541 --> 00:23:04,083
It's a hot matchup.

459
00:23:04,166 --> 00:23:06,833
The buzz will be huge
and think of the donations.

460
00:23:06,916 --> 00:23:08,875
- Wait a minute, I--
- [Aki] It's too dangerous.

461
00:23:09,458 --> 00:23:11,791
It's reckless
taking on a skilled guy like that.

462
00:23:11,875 --> 00:23:13,000
I agree.

463
00:23:13,083 --> 00:23:15,458
Sorry, but that's how it is.

464
00:23:15,541 --> 00:23:18,000
The reason the viewers are so hyped…

465
00:23:19,416 --> 00:23:21,083
is 'cause he volunteered himself!

466
00:23:21,166 --> 00:23:22,041
@REOSHINJO FIGHT ME

467
00:23:25,750 --> 00:23:26,583
IT'S HIM!

468
00:23:26,666 --> 00:23:27,875
SHINJO FOUND YOU!

469
00:23:27,958 --> 00:23:28,875
GAME OVER LOL

470
00:23:28,958 --> 00:23:29,791
No way.

471
00:23:36,541 --> 00:23:38,083
- [woman] Asamiya?
- Yeah?

472
00:23:38,166 --> 00:23:40,166
['60s pop music playing over speakers]

473
00:23:40,250 --> 00:23:41,833
Did you see this?

474
00:23:41,916 --> 00:23:43,750
VIRAL HIT'S HOT GIRLFRIEND!

475
00:23:43,833 --> 00:23:45,833
Oh, that's us.

476
00:23:45,916 --> 00:23:47,708
[man] Someone managed to figure it out

477
00:23:47,791 --> 00:23:51,625
from the video of you
on <i>Hamaken TV </i>and <i>Viral Hit.</i>

478
00:23:52,500 --> 00:23:53,583
FOUND TRUE BEAUTY!

479
00:23:53,666 --> 00:23:54,500
WIFE MATERIAL

480
00:23:54,583 --> 00:23:56,166
[woman] You should be careful.

481
00:23:56,666 --> 00:23:59,916
Let me know if any weirdos come in.
I'll tell the manager.

482
00:24:00,625 --> 00:24:01,500
Yeah.

483
00:24:03,958 --> 00:24:06,500
Don't let
these test results bring you down.

484
00:24:06,583 --> 00:24:09,333
- Your numbers will improve again.
- [sighs]

485
00:24:10,875 --> 00:24:13,333
- [boy 1] Whoa!! Awesome!
- [boy 2] He won again!

486
00:24:13,416 --> 00:24:15,875
[mother] Sh! Boys!
Keep it down. We're in hospital.

487
00:24:15,958 --> 00:24:17,375
It's okay.

488
00:24:18,625 --> 00:24:21,708
Oh, that looks fun. What are you watching?

489
00:24:21,791 --> 00:24:22,666
<i>Viral Hit</i>.

490
00:24:22,750 --> 00:24:24,666
He's super popular.

491
00:24:24,750 --> 00:24:26,833
[doctor] So, this is
what kids are into these days?

492
00:24:27,416 --> 00:24:29,708
[boy 2] I'm gonna be a streamer
when I grow up.

493
00:24:29,791 --> 00:24:32,750
[chuckles] Very good. I hope you will. Mm.

494
00:24:32,833 --> 00:24:36,000
- Thank you so much. Thank you.
- Oh! Awesome punching!

495
00:24:42,208 --> 00:24:43,625
ASAMIYA: THAT WAS FUN

496
00:24:43,708 --> 00:24:44,583
SEE YOU AT WORK

497
00:24:45,916 --> 00:24:47,625
[phone chiming]

498
00:24:48,166 --> 00:24:49,041
Hi there.

499
00:24:49,125 --> 00:24:50,625
Shimura, where are you?

500
00:24:50,708 --> 00:24:52,833
I'm heading off to work. Why?

501
00:24:52,916 --> 00:24:54,500
Aki, she's in trouble!

502
00:24:55,125 --> 00:24:57,708
[ominous music playing]

503
00:24:57,791 --> 00:24:59,708
[Shimura panting]

504
00:24:59,791 --> 00:25:01,416
<i>Don't make me repeat myself.</i>

505
00:25:02,125 --> 00:25:03,666
Shimura will not fight you.

506
00:25:03,750 --> 00:25:05,083
I wasn't asking you.

507
00:25:05,166 --> 00:25:06,625
Aki, that's enough. Let's go.

508
00:25:06,708 --> 00:25:07,791
Let me go!

509
00:25:07,875 --> 00:25:11,416
You volunteered yourself
and now the viewers are egging us on.

510
00:25:11,500 --> 00:25:12,833
Withdraw your challenge.

511
00:25:12,916 --> 00:25:14,708
Don't tell me what to do.

512
00:25:15,208 --> 00:25:18,500
- Please, Aki, let's go home. Come on!
- Aki. Are you okay?

513
00:25:19,916 --> 00:25:21,041
Did you call him?

514
00:25:21,125 --> 00:25:22,875
- I'm sorry.
- You should be ashamed.

515
00:25:22,958 --> 00:25:24,166
Let's go home, Aki.

516
00:25:24,250 --> 00:25:25,416
[Reo] Wait a second.

517
00:25:27,958 --> 00:25:28,875
Will you fight me?

518
00:25:28,958 --> 00:25:30,958
[ominous music continues]

519
00:25:32,166 --> 00:25:33,916
I'm sorry, but I won't.

520
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:35,041
You're far too strong.

521
00:25:35,125 --> 00:25:36,000
Then…

522
00:25:39,666 --> 00:25:41,333
hand over your channel.

523
00:25:42,083 --> 00:25:43,166
Huh?

524
00:25:44,083 --> 00:25:46,208
[grunts] Ah! Ah!

525
00:25:46,291 --> 00:25:49,583
- [Shimura] Kanegon!
- I know you're making bank.

526
00:25:49,666 --> 00:25:51,833
[Toru coughing]

527
00:25:51,916 --> 00:25:53,875
- Give it to me.
- [Toru hacking]

528
00:25:55,541 --> 00:25:58,833
- What are you saying? [grunts, groans]
- [Shimura] Stop this!

529
00:25:58,916 --> 00:26:00,458
[yelping] Ah! Ugh!

530
00:26:01,458 --> 00:26:04,208
Ugh! Ugh! Ugh!

531
00:26:04,291 --> 00:26:06,125
- [kicks thudding]
- [Toru grunting]

532
00:26:07,541 --> 00:26:09,000
I said stop it!

533
00:26:16,208 --> 00:26:17,250
[music fades]

534
00:26:17,333 --> 00:26:18,791
[tense music playing]

535
00:26:18,875 --> 00:26:20,250
[Reo] Hand it over.

536
00:26:20,750 --> 00:26:23,083
Stop it! You're gonna kill him!

537
00:26:23,666 --> 00:26:26,208
[screaming]

538
00:26:26,291 --> 00:26:27,458
Let go of me!

539
00:26:27,541 --> 00:26:30,833
[solemn choral music playing]

540
00:26:32,125 --> 00:26:33,333
[yelping]

541
00:26:34,208 --> 00:26:35,208
[shudders]

542
00:26:35,291 --> 00:26:36,291
[Aki choking]

543
00:26:39,750 --> 00:26:41,416
Okay! Okay, then.

544
00:26:42,208 --> 00:26:43,083
You can have it.

545
00:26:43,166 --> 00:26:47,208
Our channel, it's yours.
Just stop. Stop doing this.

546
00:26:48,750 --> 00:26:50,000
[gasps]

547
00:26:57,375 --> 00:26:59,125
Announce it in a video.

548
00:27:00,750 --> 00:27:02,208
Tell everyone.

549
00:27:08,666 --> 00:27:10,750
[music fades]

550
00:27:19,458 --> 00:27:23,375
I hear that streamers are all the craze
amongst the younger generation.

551
00:27:24,500 --> 00:27:26,125
Um, yeah, they are.

552
00:27:26,208 --> 00:27:27,916
They're even recognized by society now.

553
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:30,916
It's a cop-out for losers
who can't land a real job.

554
00:27:39,333 --> 00:27:41,583
RUMI
72,000 FOLLOWERS

555
00:27:41,666 --> 00:27:43,708
[footsteps approach]

556
00:27:43,791 --> 00:27:44,833
Here.

557
00:27:44,916 --> 00:27:47,666
My follower account
has stopped growing lately.

558
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:50,416
You'll have times like that.

559
00:27:50,916 --> 00:27:52,291
What should I do?

560
00:27:53,041 --> 00:27:53,958
Hmm.

561
00:27:54,625 --> 00:27:58,583
Well, it costs money to get exposure
and to promote you, you see.

562
00:27:58,666 --> 00:28:00,208
[eerie music playing]

563
00:28:00,291 --> 00:28:03,666
If you took on more jobs,
the cost can be offset.

564
00:28:04,583 --> 00:28:07,166
Well, that's what I'll do.
I'll take on more jobs.

565
00:28:07,250 --> 00:28:11,333
Will you? Really?
Ah, that would help out a lot.

566
00:28:11,416 --> 00:28:12,916
Our sponsors are important.

567
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:14,541
I'll do it. What is it?

568
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:19,541
The job is simple.

569
00:28:24,541 --> 00:28:26,958
That was a disaster, wasn't it?

570
00:28:28,458 --> 00:28:31,208
Things are just getting too dangerous.

571
00:28:32,291 --> 00:28:33,166
We're

572
00:28:34,333 --> 00:28:36,666
just not cut out for this, I think.

573
00:28:41,041 --> 00:28:42,416
I'm not buying it.

574
00:28:43,125 --> 00:28:43,958
Huh?

575
00:28:50,250 --> 00:28:52,333
I didn't want to hand it over.

576
00:28:53,166 --> 00:28:55,750
That's our channel. It belongs to us.

577
00:28:56,916 --> 00:28:58,958
[poignant music playing]

578
00:29:01,958 --> 00:29:04,541
When you took on Hamaken,

579
00:29:05,916 --> 00:29:06,833
I,

580
00:29:07,791 --> 00:29:10,333
truthfully, was very moved.

581
00:29:11,416 --> 00:29:14,541
If we're weak and even made fun of,

582
00:29:15,291 --> 00:29:17,125
that it's okay to be brave.

583
00:29:17,625 --> 00:29:19,375
Miracles can happen.

584
00:29:20,166 --> 00:29:21,791
So how can you…

585
00:29:23,208 --> 00:29:25,916
say that you'll give up
the channel so easily?

586
00:29:28,833 --> 00:29:30,125
[labored breathing]

587
00:29:31,333 --> 00:29:32,458
Is that…

588
00:29:33,541 --> 00:29:36,541
how little you care for <i>Viral Hit</i>
and all we've done?

589
00:29:39,166 --> 00:29:40,625
Yeah, it is.

590
00:29:41,416 --> 00:29:44,041
There's no point
taking on a guy like that for real.

591
00:29:45,041 --> 00:29:46,208
I'm not an idiot.

592
00:29:51,458 --> 00:29:52,791
[Aki] Are you okay?

593
00:29:59,625 --> 00:30:00,750
What's wrong?

594
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:04,125
[poignant music continues]

595
00:30:04,208 --> 00:30:05,458
Go away.

596
00:30:06,083 --> 00:30:07,000
What are you saying?

597
00:30:07,083 --> 00:30:08,916
- Aki came all this way--
- Just go!

598
00:30:10,625 --> 00:30:11,625
Get outta here.

599
00:30:14,333 --> 00:30:15,833
Come on, let's go.

600
00:30:28,500 --> 00:30:30,583
[grunting] Ah! Ah!

601
00:30:31,625 --> 00:30:33,958
[echoes] Stop it! You're gonna kill him!

602
00:30:34,583 --> 00:30:36,625
[groans, yelps]

603
00:30:36,708 --> 00:30:38,583
[whimpering]

604
00:30:39,916 --> 00:30:41,708
[choking, straining]

605
00:30:41,791 --> 00:30:42,666
[crying]

606
00:30:42,750 --> 00:30:44,916
[tender music playing]

607
00:30:48,166 --> 00:30:49,333
[crying]

608
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:52,500
I am such an idiot.

609
00:30:53,750 --> 00:30:56,416
<i>When Shinjo sets his sights on a target,</i>

610
00:30:56,500 --> 00:30:57,833
he attacks their friends

611
00:30:58,375 --> 00:31:00,666
rather than the target themselves.

612
00:31:02,250 --> 00:31:04,208
In front of the target.

613
00:31:06,666 --> 00:31:08,583
He's a real psychopath who gets a rush

614
00:31:08,666 --> 00:31:13,333
from leaving his opponents
totally helpless and also humiliated.

615
00:31:15,166 --> 00:31:16,666
And they…

616
00:31:18,958 --> 00:31:20,291
They say…

617
00:31:20,791 --> 00:31:23,666
he murdered
a fellow delinquent a few years ago.

618
00:31:24,333 --> 00:31:26,291
He was released
due to lack of evidence,

619
00:31:26,375 --> 00:31:28,541
but no one has been charged
with the killing.

620
00:31:28,625 --> 00:31:31,375
That's how dangerous he is.

621
00:31:33,875 --> 00:31:35,333
Someone like that…

622
00:31:36,125 --> 00:31:37,250
I won't fight.

623
00:31:52,375 --> 00:31:54,708
That's our channel. It belongs to us.

624
00:31:56,916 --> 00:31:58,250
Is that

625
00:31:59,083 --> 00:32:02,166
how little you care
for <i>Viral Hit </i>and all we've done?

626
00:32:06,666 --> 00:32:09,625
[groaning]

627
00:32:11,875 --> 00:32:15,375
- [games whirring, chattering]
- [muffled dance music playing over PA]

628
00:32:20,250 --> 00:32:21,666
[Reo] Uploaded the video yet?

629
00:32:22,750 --> 00:32:23,708
Not yet.

630
00:32:30,125 --> 00:32:33,583
As I promised,
you can have that channel to yourself.

631
00:32:34,208 --> 00:32:36,791
But… I have one condition.

632
00:32:38,833 --> 00:32:40,083
You must defeat me

633
00:32:41,041 --> 00:32:43,000
in a fight one month from now.

634
00:32:48,541 --> 00:32:50,333
Just say time and place

635
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:53,250
when you actually decide.

636
00:32:59,750 --> 00:33:01,958
So that's how it is.

637
00:33:02,041 --> 00:33:03,125
[Aki] Huh?

638
00:33:03,833 --> 00:33:06,833
What the hell are you thinking?
I told you not to do this.

639
00:33:06,916 --> 00:33:09,041
- I know, but I have.
- Take it back! Immediately!

640
00:33:09,125 --> 00:33:11,250
It's too late. We've already agreed on it.

641
00:33:14,083 --> 00:33:15,250
I knew it.

642
00:33:16,708 --> 00:33:17,708
You are an idiot.

643
00:33:17,791 --> 00:33:19,375
You keep quiet.

644
00:33:19,916 --> 00:33:23,125
Well, I'll be off.
I gotta start my training, yeah.

645
00:33:23,208 --> 00:33:24,833
Hey. Wait, Shimura.

646
00:33:26,375 --> 00:33:29,541
This time, you might not
just walk away with injuries.

647
00:33:30,500 --> 00:33:33,708
So, why… are you doing this?

648
00:33:35,583 --> 00:33:37,708
For money. Why else would I?

649
00:33:39,625 --> 00:33:41,833
[footsteps depart]

650
00:33:42,750 --> 00:33:44,375
You must be kidding!

651
00:33:44,458 --> 00:33:46,916
You just took an entire month off.

652
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:48,791
Yes, I'm sorry.

653
00:33:48,875 --> 00:33:51,250
So, how long do you want
to take off this time?

654
00:33:51,333 --> 00:33:52,916
- [jaunty music playing]
- About the same.

655
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:54,750
[scoffs] Shimura!

656
00:33:54,833 --> 00:33:57,583
Are you secretly studying abroad
or something like that?

657
00:33:57,666 --> 00:34:00,666
- Who takes leave from a part-time job?
- I'm very sorry.

658
00:34:00,750 --> 00:34:02,541
What… now you're gonna run?

659
00:34:04,208 --> 00:34:06,375
- [entry bell jangles]
- Shimura! Huh!

660
00:34:06,458 --> 00:34:07,666
Asamiya!

661
00:34:07,750 --> 00:34:09,875
I talked to the manager about your shift.

662
00:34:09,958 --> 00:34:11,750
I'm sorry for causing you trouble.

663
00:34:11,833 --> 00:34:12,708
Mm.

664
00:34:13,875 --> 00:34:16,041
Is this another fight?

665
00:34:16,125 --> 00:34:16,958
Mm.

666
00:34:17,541 --> 00:34:18,791
Oh, don't worry though.

667
00:34:18,875 --> 00:34:21,166
I've got someone I can count on.

668
00:34:21,250 --> 00:34:23,125
- I see.
- Mm.

669
00:34:23,875 --> 00:34:29,916
Tell me, would you still…
do it if your friend… wasn't there?

670
00:34:30,500 --> 00:34:33,000
[chuckles] Why are you asking me that?

671
00:34:33,083 --> 00:34:37,541
[chuckles] Well, you keep challenging
tougher opponents. I'm worried.

672
00:34:38,041 --> 00:34:40,291
Oh, that's nice.

673
00:34:42,125 --> 00:34:45,666
I was wondering…
whether we could go out again

674
00:34:45,750 --> 00:34:47,750
when my next fight is over?

675
00:34:47,833 --> 00:34:52,500
I want to tell you what I couldn't
the last time we met.

676
00:34:54,541 --> 00:34:55,875
Of course!

677
00:34:56,500 --> 00:34:57,583
It's a date, okay?

678
00:34:59,458 --> 00:35:01,416
Mm. Okay, deal!

679
00:35:01,500 --> 00:35:03,541
Mm. [giggles]

680
00:35:16,750 --> 00:35:18,125
Tae kwon do?

681
00:35:18,208 --> 00:35:20,916
I need to learn so I can win this thing.

682
00:35:21,500 --> 00:35:26,291
Well… if you can stop him
from using his legs,

683
00:35:26,375 --> 00:35:27,750
you might have a chance at winning.

684
00:35:27,833 --> 00:35:29,958
Stop him using his legs.

685
00:35:30,041 --> 00:35:34,791
But…  that's not something
a novice can accomplish in a month.

686
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:38,583
Yeah, I figured that.

687
00:35:38,666 --> 00:35:42,666
- [man] Hey, Tatsuya. Time for a spa.
- Okay.

688
00:35:42,750 --> 00:35:46,125
- Oh, sorry, I interrupted.
- No worries. Happy to help you.

689
00:35:46,208 --> 00:35:47,208
Thanks.

690
00:35:48,583 --> 00:35:50,291
- Here you go.
- Let's do it.

691
00:35:53,875 --> 00:35:56,583
[door opens, closes]

692
00:35:59,666 --> 00:36:01,416
[Shimura] Oh, nothing.

693
00:36:11,291 --> 00:36:12,750
[man 1] He's here, Sir.

694
00:36:14,291 --> 00:36:15,750
- [man 2 groans]
- This way.

695
00:36:16,291 --> 00:36:18,625
[tense music playing]

696
00:36:20,375 --> 00:36:21,750
[echoing] That's BAD FELLOWS.

697
00:36:21,833 --> 00:36:22,750
Who are they?

698
00:36:22,833 --> 00:36:23,791
You don't know?

699
00:36:23,875 --> 00:36:28,375
It's a super popular show that pits
amateur fighters against each other.

700
00:36:29,625 --> 00:36:32,958
- Are you Shimura from <i>Viral Hit</i>?
- Uh, yes.

701
00:36:35,500 --> 00:36:38,625
I'm the representative of BAD FELLOWS,

702
00:36:39,125 --> 00:36:40,291
I'm Kuwata.

703
00:36:40,375 --> 00:36:42,958
Oh, yes. I've heard of you.

704
00:36:43,458 --> 00:36:44,750
That makes things easier.

705
00:36:44,833 --> 00:36:46,375
What do you say?

706
00:36:47,166 --> 00:36:49,708
Would you star in our show?

707
00:36:49,791 --> 00:36:50,916
Hey?

708
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:53,750
You could become
even more famous than you are now.

709
00:36:54,750 --> 00:36:55,666
Oh

710
00:36:56,916 --> 00:36:58,458
Uh, wow.

711
00:36:58,541 --> 00:37:00,666
Sorry, I'm not interested
in that kind of thing.

712
00:37:00,750 --> 00:37:01,916
Hmm?

713
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:05,916
I guess it's just… I mean, I'm not looking
to become a professional fighter.

714
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:08,541
And I'm not interested in becoming famous.

715
00:37:09,541 --> 00:37:10,458
Okay.

716
00:37:12,333 --> 00:37:15,416
Well… if you ever do need money,

717
00:37:15,916 --> 00:37:17,375
please come to me anytime.

718
00:37:17,458 --> 00:37:18,916
I'd be glad to help you.

719
00:37:25,208 --> 00:37:27,291
[door opens]

720
00:37:27,375 --> 00:37:29,458
[door closes]

721
00:37:30,958 --> 00:37:31,833
[Kuwata] Hmm.

722
00:37:32,708 --> 00:37:33,875
- And there you are.
- Thank you.

723
00:37:33,958 --> 00:37:34,791
There's your change.

724
00:37:34,875 --> 00:37:36,416
- Thank you very much.
- Thank you so much.

725
00:37:36,500 --> 00:37:38,583
- Thanks, have a nice day.
- [woman] That was delicious.

726
00:37:38,666 --> 00:37:40,708
- [door opens]
- [bell jangles]

727
00:37:40,791 --> 00:37:41,958
- [door closes]
- [bell jangles]

728
00:37:42,041 --> 00:37:45,291
- Okay, who's next?
- ['60s pop music playing over PA]

729
00:37:45,375 --> 00:37:46,791
Dad.

730
00:37:49,541 --> 00:37:51,416
VIRAL HIT'S HOT GIRLFRIEND!

731
00:37:54,458 --> 00:37:56,875
[Hamaken on video] <i>You're so annoying,</i>
<i>you piece of trash!</i>

732
00:37:56,958 --> 00:37:59,458
[Shimura] <i>I'm not a loser,</i>
<i>but you're a loser for sure!</i>

733
00:37:59,541 --> 00:38:00,416
[Hamaken groans]

734
00:38:07,333 --> 00:38:08,750
[sighs]

735
00:38:13,083 --> 00:38:14,416
[phone chimes]

736
00:38:18,500 --> 00:38:20,916
[man] <i>Any more would be dangerous.</i>

737
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:21,833
LOGAN

738
00:38:22,833 --> 00:38:24,833
[pensive music playing]

739
00:38:25,666 --> 00:38:26,833
[grunting]

740
00:38:35,833 --> 00:38:37,291
[phone chimes]

741
00:38:38,500 --> 00:38:40,791
NEW VIDEO FROM HOW_TO_FIGHT

742
00:38:45,625 --> 00:38:49,583
HOW A NOVICE CAN BEAT
A TAE KWON DO FIGHTER

743
00:38:53,583 --> 00:38:54,875
[music fades]

744
00:38:54,958 --> 00:38:57,125
ONE MONTH LATER

745
00:38:57,208 --> 00:38:59,208
[dramatic rock music playing]

746
00:39:14,291 --> 00:39:15,375
Let's go.

747
00:39:20,708 --> 00:39:21,541
[Aki] <i>They say</i>

748
00:39:22,500 --> 00:39:25,458
he murdered
a fellow delinquent a few years ago.

749
00:39:53,875 --> 00:39:56,083
[Toru] What? Shimura, where are you going?

750
00:39:56,166 --> 00:39:57,166
He's fast.

751
00:39:57,250 --> 00:39:59,125
[tense music playingj]

752
00:40:12,541 --> 00:40:14,833
[Shimura] <i>Fighting mindset,</i>
<i>rule number one.</i>

753
00:40:16,208 --> 00:40:18,083
<i>Make your opponent lose his cool.</i>

754
00:40:18,666 --> 00:40:20,291
You little…

755
00:40:22,041 --> 00:40:23,166
What are you doing?

756
00:40:24,125 --> 00:40:27,166
[Toru] You stay here.
We'll use this to talk.

757
00:40:27,250 --> 00:40:29,208
But why can't I come?

758
00:40:29,291 --> 00:40:31,166
I want to handle this alone.

759
00:40:32,458 --> 00:40:35,416
I don't want you to see me…
when I'm frightened.

760
00:40:37,125 --> 00:40:38,458
IT'S ALREADY STARTED!

761
00:40:38,541 --> 00:40:39,458
GO! SHIMURA!

762
00:40:39,541 --> 00:40:40,833
IS HE SPRAYING WATER?

763
00:40:40,916 --> 00:40:42,500
I NEED YOU TO WIN, SHIMURA

764
00:40:42,583 --> 00:40:43,750
I'M SWEATING LOLOL

765
00:40:43,833 --> 00:40:45,041
IT'S HAPPENING!!!

766
00:40:47,958 --> 00:40:49,041
[drops hose]

767
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:52,250
[exhales]

768
00:40:52,333 --> 00:40:53,500
[whooshing]

769
00:40:59,666 --> 00:41:01,625
Keep your eyes shut, and you're dead.

770
00:41:02,333 --> 00:41:05,708
<i>How to beat a tae kwon do fighter,</i>
<i>rule one.</i>

771
00:41:06,750 --> 00:41:09,583
<i>Take control of the space</i>
<i>so they can't use their feet.</i>

772
00:41:11,208 --> 00:41:12,791
[Shimura grunting]

773
00:41:12,875 --> 00:41:14,083
[groans]

774
00:41:14,166 --> 00:41:15,583
[grunting]

775
00:41:15,666 --> 00:41:16,500
Dumbass.

776
00:41:16,583 --> 00:41:18,916
You thought you could win
by splashing water?

777
00:41:19,000 --> 00:41:19,833
[straining]

778
00:41:19,916 --> 00:41:21,541
[gasping]

779
00:41:21,625 --> 00:41:23,625
What made you think I'd only kick?

780
00:41:24,333 --> 00:41:26,541
[Shimura groaning]

781
00:41:29,333 --> 00:41:32,291
This is… a fight, right?

782
00:41:40,416 --> 00:41:42,666
[Shimura grunting]

783
00:41:44,583 --> 00:41:45,791
You're right.

784
00:41:45,875 --> 00:41:47,875
This is a fight.

785
00:41:49,458 --> 00:41:50,583
[squeaks]

786
00:41:51,208 --> 00:41:52,833
WHY ISN'T SHIMURA SLIPPING?

787
00:41:52,916 --> 00:41:54,416
HE'S WEARING WATER SHOES!

788
00:41:54,500 --> 00:41:56,000
THAT'S SNEAKY LOL

789
00:41:57,958 --> 00:42:01,250
[Shimura grunting]

790
00:42:06,958 --> 00:42:09,250
[Shimura] <i>It's not over yet.</i>
<i>We've barely begun.</i>

791
00:42:14,375 --> 00:42:15,791
[grunting continues]

792
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:22,666
[TOU-KEI] <i>Nothing in the world frustrates</i>
<i>a kicker a more</i>

793
00:42:23,750 --> 00:42:25,333
<i>than a tackle.</i>

794
00:42:26,708 --> 00:42:31,625
<i>The key to a successful tackle is</i>
<i>to grab the back of the knees.</i>

795
00:42:31,708 --> 00:42:35,125
<i>Grab and pull</i>
<i>at the back of your opponent's knees.</i>

796
00:42:35,208 --> 00:42:41,083
<i>You can take down even a large opponent.</i>
<i>This is the double leg tackle!</i>

797
00:42:41,750 --> 00:42:42,875
Yeah!

798
00:42:42,958 --> 00:42:44,541
[music intensifies]

799
00:42:44,625 --> 00:42:50,291
[TOU-KEI] <i>If the takedown is successful,</i>
<i>your odds jump past 50%.</i>

800
00:42:51,666 --> 00:42:56,625
<i>But you must never swing</i>
<i>your fist from above.</i>

801
00:42:57,291 --> 00:43:01,416
<i>You only get one chance</i>
<i>against a martial opponent.</i>

802
00:43:01,916 --> 00:43:04,750
<i>You must finish them off in one blow.</i>

803
00:43:07,416 --> 00:43:10,333
<i>Put your hand behind your opponent's neck,</i>

804
00:43:10,416 --> 00:43:13,416
<i>grab their collar and pull them close.</i>

805
00:43:14,125 --> 00:43:16,375
[grunting]

806
00:43:18,041 --> 00:43:20,625
[both straining]

807
00:43:23,416 --> 00:43:27,500
[TOU-KEI] <i>Even if your opponent resists,</i>
<i>don't let go!</i>

808
00:43:28,375 --> 00:43:31,500
<i>This is a technique</i>
<i>that compresses the carotid artery.</i>

809
00:43:31,583 --> 00:43:33,416
<i>The cross choke!</i>

810
00:43:33,500 --> 00:43:37,458
<i>It takes ten seconds</i>
<i>for your opponent to pass out.</i>

811
00:43:37,541 --> 00:43:40,875
<i>So, count it out in your head.</i>

812
00:43:42,166 --> 00:43:43,208
[Shimura] <i>One…</i>

813
00:43:43,708 --> 00:43:44,916
<i>Two…</i>

814
00:43:45,000 --> 00:43:46,375
<i>- </i>Yeah!
<i>- Three…</i>

815
00:43:47,041 --> 00:43:48,125
<i>Four…</i>

816
00:43:48,958 --> 00:43:50,125
<i>Five…</i>

817
00:43:50,208 --> 00:43:51,916
- [students murmur]
<i>- </i>[Shimura] <i>Six…</i>

818
00:43:52,500 --> 00:43:53,458
<i>Seven…</i>

819
00:43:53,958 --> 00:43:55,208
<i>Eight…</i>

820
00:43:55,708 --> 00:43:57,291
<i>Nine…</i>

821
00:43:59,041 --> 00:43:59,875
HUH?

822
00:43:59,958 --> 00:44:03,083
SHINJO DOESN'T LOOK WORRIED

823
00:44:03,166 --> 00:44:04,791
YOU'RE RIGHT LOLOL

824
00:44:04,875 --> 00:44:06,250
[Shimura straining]

825
00:44:06,333 --> 00:44:09,208
- That's bad, the choke came off.
- [Shimura groans]

826
00:44:10,625 --> 00:44:11,750
Idiot.

827
00:44:12,708 --> 00:44:15,041
- You didn't land it right.
- [gasps]

828
00:44:15,125 --> 00:44:18,541
[Shimura grunting]

829
00:44:18,625 --> 00:44:19,625
Shimura!

830
00:44:20,125 --> 00:44:21,250
ALMOST HAD IT!

831
00:44:21,333 --> 00:44:22,708
YOU WERE SO CLOSE!

832
00:44:22,791 --> 00:44:26,166
Oh no.
Shinjo allowed the hold deliberately.

833
00:44:27,041 --> 00:44:28,041
Huh?

834
00:44:29,208 --> 00:44:31,708
[Reo] You really thought
I'd fall for that move?

835
00:44:32,458 --> 00:44:34,625
[breathing heavily, sniffs]

836
00:44:34,708 --> 00:44:36,125
This is what I wanted.8

837
00:44:37,458 --> 00:44:38,750
[shoe plops]

838
00:44:40,833 --> 00:44:42,666
[TOU-KEI] <i>Remember, the only way</i>

839
00:44:42,750 --> 00:44:45,333
<i>for an amateur to beat</i>
<i>a tae kwon do fighter</i>

840
00:44:45,416 --> 00:44:47,833
<i>is to steal their kicks.</i>

841
00:44:48,666 --> 00:44:50,875
Now I can use the legs.

842
00:44:52,666 --> 00:44:57,750
[TOU-KEI] <i>And if you fail to do that,</i>
<i>there's only one thing left to do.</i>

843
00:44:59,375 --> 00:45:02,791
<i>- Run for your life!</i>
- [alarm blaring]

844
00:45:03,583 --> 00:45:04,500
[gasps]

845
00:45:05,125 --> 00:45:06,750
- [kick thuds]
- [Shimura groans]

846
00:45:07,416 --> 00:45:08,958
[Toru] Shimura!

847
00:45:09,041 --> 00:45:11,291
It's too dangerous. Run!

848
00:45:13,291 --> 00:45:14,833
[Shimura] <i>I'm such an idiot.</i>

849
00:45:15,708 --> 00:45:17,833
<i>Especially after all of that practice.</i>

850
00:45:20,666 --> 00:45:23,375
[Shimura groaning, grunting]

851
00:45:31,083 --> 00:45:32,375
Oh shit.

852
00:45:32,458 --> 00:45:34,708
This guy, he's gonna kill Shimura.

853
00:45:39,541 --> 00:45:43,833
[solemn choral music playing]

854
00:45:48,125 --> 00:45:53,291
[approaching sirens wailing]

855
00:46:01,500 --> 00:46:05,958
[gasping]

856
00:46:06,583 --> 00:46:09,250
[Japanese rock music playing]

857
00:46:18,416 --> 00:46:25,416
VIRAL HIT

858
00:46:30,625 --> 00:46:32,625
[Japanese rock music continues]

859
00:47:42,041 --> 00:47:43,041
[music ends]
